<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Background_2">Background</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=That%27ll_Be_the_Day&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Background">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p><a href="/wiki/Linda_Ronstadt" title="Linda Ronstadt">Linda Ronstadt</a> recorded a cover version of "That'll Be the Day" for her 1976 Grammy Award–winning <a href="/wiki/Platinum_album" class="mw-redirect" title="Platinum album">platinum album</a> <i><a href="/wiki/Hasten_Down_the_Wind" title="Hasten Down the Wind">Hasten Down the Wind</a></i>, produced by <a href="/wiki/Peter_Asher" title="Peter Asher">Peter Asher</a> and issued by <a href="/wiki/Asylum_Records" title="Asylum Records">Asylum Records</a>. Her version reached number 11 on both the U.S. <a href="/wiki/Billboard_Hot_100" title="Billboard Hot 100"><i>Billboard</i> Hot 100</a> and the <i><a href="/wiki/Cash_Box" class="mw-redirect" title="Cash Box">Cash Box</a></i> Top 100 and number 27 on the <i>Billboard</i> Country Singles chart. In Canada, her version peaked at number 2 on the singles chart and was the 35th biggest hit of 1976. It also made the <a href="/wiki/Adult_contemporary" class="mw-redirect" title="Adult contemporary">adult contemporary</a> charts in the United States and Canada. This recording is included on the album <i><a href="/wiki/Linda_Ronstadt%27s_Greatest_Hits" class="mw-redirect" title="Linda Ronstadt's Greatest Hits">Linda Ronstadt's Greatest Hits</a></i> (1976) and on the 2011 tribute album <i><a href="/wiki/Listen_to_Me:_Buddy_Holly" title="Listen to Me: Buddy Holly">Listen to Me: Buddy Holly</a></i>.</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Chart_performance">Chart performance</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=That%27ll_Be_the_Day&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Chart performance">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
